title: Cant see Match History at All
body: What the title says,  cant see any match history (my own and as well as others).

replies.body:
Are you trying to view match history from inside the League client or from the[ match history section](http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-history) of the site?

Let me know, thanks!
Yes, from the site. The site is just blank. I've tried in both Chrome and Edge none of them works. Everything is fine in the client and on other sites (like op.gg)

I recommend [clearing your browser cache](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies) or using *incognito mode* in chrome.

Let me know if either resolved this.

tried both, no success. It looks like this http://imgur.com/a/41HLl

I get the same result across different browsers (and on mobile).

If it's still not working, then it's related to a known bug with that page. Feel free to report this bug on our [Bug Tracker](http://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/bug-report) so we can keep an eye on it.

Let me know if you have any other questions.

I've been seeing match history fail to load for more than a week now. This seems to happen with all matches (I've been testing it on group stage Worlds matches) and across Chrome, Chrome Incognito, Firefox, and Edge (most of which have no add-ons enabled).

Specific details on the failure: the actual page will load, but the white section-wrapper-content-wrapper div on the page which is supposed to fill with all the match details remains unfilled and only about 1/3rd of the page height.

I just thought to check the JavaScript console in Chrome, and the following errors display:
/en/#match-details/TRLH1/1001890201?gameHash=6751c4ef7ef58654:8 X-Frame-Options may only be set via an HTTP header sent along with a document. It may not be set inside <meta>.
twig.js:3625 Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input
ramen.js:24 Uncaught ReferenceError: Twig is not defined
http://riot-dradis-assets-oregon.s3.amazonaws.com/dradis-0.5.0-prod.min.js Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 403 (Forbidden)
analytics.min.js:4 Uncaught ReferenceError: Dradis is not defined

to WATCH match history it tells you to go to the site and the match history box is just blank white
w/e the client shows me everything except a replay of the match
